                },
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "Materials in this collection were placed in new acid-free folders and boxes. Original caption information, was transcribed onto archival folders. The collection was arranged into two series based on the original order of the records and original folder titles were retained."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "scopecontent": [
            {
                "id": "aspace_ea72ab5b94946223cc0df7fe4198b20e",
                "head": {
                    "value": "Scope and Contents"
                },
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "This collection mainly consists of photocopies of Silverman's research findings, detailed notes and annotations for his 1991 biography, \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eEdgar A Poe: Mournful and Never-Ending Remembrance\u003c/span\u003e. The photocopied research materials give an overview of Edgar Allan Poe's personal and professional life ranging from his childhood, family history  and romantic relationships with alleged fiance Sarah Elmira Royster and wife Virginia Poe. They consist of correspondence and journal entries from various manuscript and archival collections across the United States, maps of Poe's homes in various cities such as  Baltimore and Philadelphia, newspaper articles and book extractions from about 1800 to the late 1890s. Silverman was also well known for his research intensive writing process. The Kenneth Silverman Papers is a reflection of this process."
                    }
                ]
            }
